<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 75.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 2d of June last, No. 77, and accompanying
                            correspondence, respecting the case of James White. With regard to the
                            pressing need of increased assistance in the different branches of our
                            service in China, so reasonably solicited and supported by yourself and
                            by Mr. Seward, I shall not fail to make a representation to Congress on
                            the subject, at its ensuing session.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>